# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Lustra frontend — UAT (Vercel)
#
# Set these in Vercel: Project → Settings → Environment Variables.
# Scope them to the environment that serves https://uat.lustra.vip.
#
# EVERY VITE_* VALUE IS COMPILED INTO THE PUBLIC BROWSER BUNDLE.
# It is readable by anyone who loads the site. Never put an R2 credential, a JWT
# signing key, a database connection string or a private bucket name here.
# Authorization is enforced by the .NET API, never by these values.
#
# Validated by src/config/env.ts at startup. There is NO silent fallback from
# api → mock: a missing API base URL renders a configuration error instead of
# quietly serving fixtures.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Real API. A production build refuses to run in mock mode.
VITE_DATA_MODE=api

# Must include the /api/v1 suffix, and must be https — an https page cannot call
# an http API, the browser blocks it as mixed content.
# REPLACE once the API host exists; it is not yet deployed.
VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://uatapi.lustra.vip/api/v1

# SignalR hub ORIGIN — no /api/v1 suffix. Defaults to the API origin if unset;
# set it explicitly so a future API path change cannot silently break chat.
VITE_SIGNALR_BASE_URL=https://uatapi.lustra.vip

# Marks the build as UAT.
VITE_APP_ENV=uat

# Never enable outside local development. It is force-disabled in production
# builds regardless, and it never grants real server permissions — the API
# remains the authorization boundary — but it must not be advertised in UAT.
VITE_ENABLE_DEV_ROLE_SWITCHER=false

VITE_ENABLE_QUERY_DEVTOOLS=false

# No public media base URL is set on purpose. The API returns absolute,
# access-checked media URLs and authorises VIP media per request. Introducing a
# public media base URL here would move an authorization decision into the
# browser bundle.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# TROUBLESHOOTING — the two UAT failures seen on 2026-07-21
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# 1) Browser blocks the CORS preflight on
#      https://uatapi.lustra.vip/public/talents
#
#    ONE fault, in the Vercel value rather than the code: the /api/v1 suffix
#    was MISSING.
#
#    The hostname was right all along — uatapi.lustra.vip, no hyphen. Every
#    backend route is api/v1/... (PublicTalentsController is
#    [Route("api/v1/public/talents")]), so without the suffix the request lands
#    on a path the API redirects rather than serves. A redirect during a CORS
#    preflight is refused by the browser, and the console blames CORS while the
#    cause is the URL.
#
#    Set VITE_API_BASE_URL to the value above — complete, and with no trailing
#    slash — then REDEPLOY. Vite bakes this in at build time, so changing the
#    variable without rebuilding changes nothing.
#
#    A production build now refuses to start if this value is http://, points
#    at localhost, is relative, or is missing the /api/v1 suffix. The page shows
#    a configuration error naming the problem instead of a misleading CORS
#    failure. See deployedApiBaseUrlProblems() in src/config/env.ts.
#
# 2) GET https://uat.lustra.vip/logo_x.png returns 404
#
#    Fixed in the code. The asset is public/Logo_x.png — CAPITAL L, which is how
#    git records it and therefore how Vercel checks it out on Linux. The header
#    component asked for the lowercase spelling, which works on Windows
#    (core.ignorecase=true) and 404s on every deployed environment.
#
# ── Caching: what a tester must do after the fix is deployed ─────────────────
#
# This app registers NO service worker — there is no PWA cache to clear, and no
# offline cache can pin an old bundle. (public/manifest.json only makes the app
# installable.) JS bundles are content-hashed and index.html is served
# must-revalidate by vercel.json, so a new deploy is picked up on reload.
#
# If a tester still sees the old API host after a redeploy, it is ordinary
# browser or CDN caching:
#   1. Hard reload (Ctrl+F5 / Cmd+Shift+R).
#   2. DevTools → Application → Storage → "Clear site data", then reload.
#   3. DevTools → Application → Service workers: confirm NONE is registered. If
#      one is listed it is left over from an earlier experiment — click
#      "Unregister" and reload.
#   4. Confirm the deployment actually rebuilt: a Vercel env-var change alone
#      does not rebuild, because Vite inlines these values at build time.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# WHERE THESE VALUES ACTUALLY COME FROM
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Three layers, highest priority first:
#
#   1. Vercel dashboard variables            AUTHORITATIVE
#   2. .env.local                            local only, never committed
#   3. .env.uat / .env.production            committed fallbacks
#
# Verified, not assumed: a build with a conflicting VITE_API_BASE_URL in the
# process environment produced the process value in the bundle, not the file
# value. Vite applies process.env AFTER the .env files.
#
# ⚠️ VERCEL CHANGES REQUIRE A REDEPLOY. Vite inlines every VITE_* value at BUILD
#    time — they are baked into the JavaScript, not read at runtime. Editing a
#    variable in the dashboard changes nothing until the project is rebuilt.
#
# ⚠️ SET THE UAT PROJECT'S BUILD COMMAND TO `npm run build:uat`.
#    The default `npm run build` runs in production mode and therefore loads
#    .env.production — so if the UAT project's dashboard variables were ever
#    missing or misspelled, the build would silently fall back to the LIVE API
#    and UAT testers would be messaging real clients. `build:uat` loads
#    .env.uat, making the fallback safe.
#
# Local development against the UAT backend:
#
#   npm run dev:uat        # loads .env.uat, talks to https://uatapi.lustra.vip
#
# A .env.local may instead mirror UAT and is git-ignored, so personal overrides
# and any tunnel URL stay off the repository.
#
# ⚠️ THE UAT BACKEND WILL REJECT localhost UNTIL IT IS ALLOWED EXPLICITLY.
#    CORS is deny-by-default with exact origins — there is no wildcard, and one
#    must not be added. Vite serves on http://localhost:5173 by default; use
#    whatever origin it actually prints, INCLUDING the port and the scheme, and
#    add it to the UAT API:
#
#      Cors__AllowedOrigins__1=http://localhost:5173
#      R2Storage__AllowedOrigins__1=http://localhost:5173
#
#    The R2 entry is applied in the Cloudflare bucket's CORS policy, not read by
#    the API — without it, direct-to-bucket media uploads fail from localhost
#    even though the REST calls succeed.
#
#    Restart the API after changing CORS. Remove both entries when finished:
#    a live-adjacent environment should not keep trusting a developer laptop.
